main event: A round gray object, smaller than a dime, was observed via ground radar in Lewiston, Washington for 50 minutes on October 16, 1951.
interesting points: The observed object was determined to be the planet Venus,The object's color was described as medium gray,The object was smaller than a dime,The observation was made by pilots flying directly at the object for an extended period, Photographs of the object did not develop properly.
